Modeled as a normalized coastal exposure gradient using general coastal corrosion behavior findings and region-specific environmental patterns.   Interprets component vulnerability categories based on commonly observed corrosion points in humid marine-adjacent areas.   No customer addresses, no individualized service tickets, and no personally identifying details are included.   Limitations: This is an aggregated risk framework intended for planning and education. Actual risk varies with building envelope design, ventilation, component material selection, and maintenance history.

Comprehensive test framework (380+ test cases) comparing Octocode MCP local tools against Claude Code and Cursor built-in tools across 9 test suites. Covers four tool categories: code search, directory listing, file reading, and file finding. Tests span 10 dimensions: context quality, efficiency, output quality, token safety, security, error handling, research context, large file handling, large repository scale, and monorepo awareness. Includes actual test results from the Linux kernel (100K+ files) showing Octocode winning on structured output, pagination, metadata richness, and token efficiency. Claude Code wins on multimodal files, shell access, and agent delegation. Prioritized acceptance criteria (P0-P3) and phased execution plan included.
